#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn29.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn29.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 29 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 29 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn29.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Nāgavagga "
msgstr "1. Dragons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn29.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Uposathasutta "
msgstr "3. Sabbath "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn29.3:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "sn29.3:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

# NOTE: See https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-dragons-and-human-sacrifice/2981
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn29.3:1.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce aṇḍajā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why some egg-born dragons keep the sabbath, having transformed their bodies?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn29.3:2.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, ekaccānaṃ aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“Mendicant, it’s when some egg-born dragons think: "

msgctxt "sn29.3:2.2"
msgid "‘mayaṃ kho pubbe kāyena dvayakārino ahumha, vācāya dvayakārino, manasā dvayakārino. "
msgstr "‘In the past we did both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn29.3:2.3"
msgid "Te mayaṃ kāyena dvayakārino, vācāya dvayakārino, manasā dvayakārino, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapannā. "
msgstr "When the body broke up, after death, we were reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons. "

msgctxt "sn29.3:2.4"
msgid "Sacajja mayaṃ kāyena sucaritaṃ careyyāma, vācāya sucaritaṃ careyyāma, manasā sucaritaṃ careyyāma, evaṃ mayaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyāma. "
msgstr "If today we do good things by body, speech, and mind, when the body breaks up, after death, we may be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "sn29.3:2.5"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ etarahi kāyena sucaritaṃ carāma, vācāya sucaritaṃ carāma, manasā sucaritaṃ carāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Come, let us do good things by way of body, speech, and mind.’ "

msgctxt "sn29.3:2.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce aṇḍajā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti. "
msgstr "This is the cause, this is the reason why some egg-born dragons keep the sabbath, having transformed their bodies.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn29.3:2.7"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

